1
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:03,880
(SCREAMING)

2
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:05,600
They've kidnapped Osgood

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:08,400
and they've stolen
the location of every Zygon on Earth.

4
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:10,360
Doctor, the ceasefire
has broken down.

5
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:11,600
Call me now.

6
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:14,720
They turned into monsters
and they came for us.

7
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,560
We couldn't fight them.
You can't tell who's who.

8
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:20,960
Oh, come on. These are
eggs or pods or whatever.

9
00:00:21,040 --> 00:00:22,040
Look.

10
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:23,920
Oh, my God, that's me.

11
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,320
But I don't see how
these are duplicates.

12
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,880
That's not how Zygons work.

13
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:31,360
These are the humans.

14
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:33,080
-Please.
-Kill the traitors.

15
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:35,680
There isn't any back-up,
is there?

16
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:41,040
(GROWLING)

17
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:46,000
UNIT neutralised in the UK.
More or less.

18
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:47,320
(BEEPS)

19
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:50,720
I'm sorry, but Clara's dead.

20
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:04,800
(BUZZING)

21
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,760
(PANTING)

22
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,160
(GASPS)

23
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,040
DOCTOR: Clara!

24
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,840
Clara!

25
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:02,080
BONNIE: You're breaking up!

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,160
DOCTOR:
The invasion has happened.

27
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:08,000
You're probably
surrounded by Zygons.

28
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,960
Get to the Tardis.
Get yourself safe.

29
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:11,840
Apparently, my plane
ls never going to land.

30
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:14,320
Well let's see
what we can do about that.

31
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:18,200
BONNIE:
I'm sorry, but Clara's dead.

32
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:22,000
(BEEPING)

33
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:55,160
Dream jets.

34
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,080
Dream jets, dream jets.

35
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,280
BONNIE:
It's your decision, Doctor.

36
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:12,920
Truth or consequences.

37
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,800
Doctor?

38
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,520
Missed!

39
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,120
(GRUNTING)

40
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,680
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

41
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:52,680
(BUZZING)

42
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:55,480
(PANTING)

43
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,600
(BOTH GROANING)

44
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:06,280
Oh!

45
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,520
(THUMPING ON DOOR)

46
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,920
(GASPING)

47
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,840
-I know what you are.
-(GASPS)

48
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:48,520
Please, please.

49
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,360
I'm going to set you free.

50
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,640
(PANTING)

51
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:57,360
Humans cannot accept
the way we really are.

52
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,320
If we cannot hide,
we must fight.

53
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,720
You are going to be the first.

54
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:05,240
The first to
make the humans see.

55
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,280
(BUZZING)

56
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,160
(GURGLING)

57
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,080
(GURGLING)

58
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,280
(GROANING)

59
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:35,040
Help me. Help me.

60
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,160
Help.

61
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,680
Help me.

62
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:43,480
(GURGLING)

63
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,440
(SIREN WAILING)

64
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,040
(GRUNTING)

65
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,280
(BEEPS)

66
00:06:57,360 --> 00:07:00,080
Commander here.
The first one has been changed.

67
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:02,680
I'm going to UNIT to
retrieve the Osgood box.

68
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:18,200
(CLICKS)

69
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,640
(HEAVY BREATHING)

70
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,240
Doctor?

71
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,400
Doctor?

72
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,200
Any questions?

73
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,400
Why do you have
a Union Jack parachute?

74
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,040
Um, camouflage.

75
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,840
-Camouflage?
-Yes, we're in Britain.

76
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:03,200
-(PANTING)
-Oh, your specs are broken.

77
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:05,560
I'll fix them.
You can wear mine, they're sonic.

78
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,040
-Sonic specs?
-Yeah!

79
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:10,360
Isn't that a bit pointless?
Like a visual hearing aid?

80
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,920
What's wrong with pointless?

81
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:16,200
I once invented an invisible watch.
Spot the design flaw.

82
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:19,040
You're talking nonsense to distract
me from being really scared.

83
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,480
It's one of your
known character traits.

84
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:24,160
-Don't look at my browser history.
-(BUZZING)

85
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,360
-Whoa.
-Yeah, I said don't.

86
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,040
Why didn't that Zygon
blow us up with her big bazooka?

87
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,440
She did blow us up
with her big bazooka.

88
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,200
This is us being blown up
with a big bazooka.

89
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,200
But I mean, she seems to know
what she's doing.

90
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:47,400
The first thing I'd do if I wanted to
invade the world would be to kill you.

91
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,480
-Thanks.
-I wouldn't even let you get talking.

92
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:51,960
Like you always do.
Bullet between the eyes, first thing.

93
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:54,760
-Again, thank you.
-I'd do it 12 times if necessary.

94
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,280
Ah, yes.
Well, why limit yourself?

95
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,880
You've really thought
this through, haven't you?

96
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:01,280
I am a big fan.
But she gave you a chance to get out.

97
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,680
She hesitated.

98
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,000
If she had
Clara's memory print,

99
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,600
she'd know better
than to give you even a second.

100
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,440
You've gone quiet
'cause I mentioned Clara.

101
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:11,760
You think she might be dead.

102
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:15,040
-Yes.
-Are you okay?

103
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:18,840
I don't know. (EXHALES)
I'm still in the hope phase.

104
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:20,320
How's that going?

105
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,840
Hell, please,
talk about something else.

106
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:41,920
(PHONE CHIMES)

107
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,240
Why did they want to
destroy the ceasefire?

108
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,560
Don't think of
them as rational, they're different.

109
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,680
They don't care
about human beings.

110
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:50,840
They don't care
about their own people.

111
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,600
They think the rest of
Zygon-kind are traitors.

112
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,800
-It's a splinter group...
-(MOBILE RINGS)

113
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,280
(BEEPING)

114
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,400
Clara.

115
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,080
Well, not Clara.
The Zygon who...

116
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,960
The Zygon who
probably killed her. Read it.

117
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:07,040
It says, "I'm awake".

118
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,920
What does that mean?
A political awakening?

119
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,360
Why would she be
sending me propaganda

120
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,560
when she just blew me up
with a big bazooka.

121
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:16,400
Never really met Clara.
Pretty strong, yeah?

122
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,320
She was amazing.

123
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:23,120
No. Not was, is.

124
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,600
It's not from the Zygon,
it's from Clara.

125
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,400
-How?
-She's not dead.

126
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,040
She's in a pod somewhere.

127
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,280
They need a live feed
to the information in her brain,

128
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,560
but she's fighting back.

129
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,800
She's trying to take control
piece by piece.

130
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:35,920
Texting?

131
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,680
How much more
human could you get?

132
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,400
The Zygon probably
doesn't even know it sent this.

133
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,960
Or why it
misfired that bazooka.

134
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,760
You don't know,
it's just a theory.

135
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:47,400
Yes it's just a theory,
but how's that hope phase now?

136
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,600
Worse than ever.

137
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,120
Then we've got a game.

138
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,280
(BEEPING)

139
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:25,960
(UNLOCKS AND BEEPS)

140
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:41,440
Hello, if you're watching this,

141
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:43,440
I have been captured
and interrogated.

142
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,600
During the interrogation,

143
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:47,600
I've revealed to you
the existence of the Osgood box.

144
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:51,160
I've revealed its location
and the combination to open this safe.

145
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,920
-And guess what?
-BOTH: 7 lied.

146
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:59,000
The Osgood box exists, but it's not
here, so stop looking. Really, stop.

147
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:02,520
The Osgood box
can end the ceasefire.

148
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,840
The Osgood box
can start the war.

149
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:07,360
The Osgood box can
wipe out all humankind.

150
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,720
But there's a reason
it's called the Osgood box.

151
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,040
Haven't you guessed?

152
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,520
(SNARLING)

153
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,880
(SHRIEKING IN RAGE)

154
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,640
(GRUNTING)

155
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,200
Hello! Hi.

156
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:24,680
Hello.

157
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:29,160
Dr John Disco. It was my plane.

158
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:33,880
I had a big plane for purposes
of poncing about.

159
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,840
It went off with a massive
bang about half a mile that way.

160
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,360
Actually, uh...

161
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:50,080
-It's fine, we're fine, aren't we?
-Yeah, yeah.

162
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:53,880
Yes, yes. We're fine.
Just, uh, move along.

163
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,480
(RINGING)

164
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,120
She's answered.

165
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:08,200
-Hello.
-You're dead.

166
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:12,400
Yes, well, I'm dead now and I think I
might be a bit more dead in a minute.

167
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:15,440
-What's your plan, Zygella?
-I don't have a plan.

168
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:18,360
Come on, you don't invade
planets without having a plan.

169
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,480
That's why they're called
planets, to remind you to plan it.

170
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,840
(CHUCKLES) Hey, that's good.
Puntastic.

171
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:26,560
Dr Puntastic. Oh, come on.
That was a good one, Zygella.

172
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:30,240
Don't call me Zygella,
my name's Bonnie.

173
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,360
You're winking at me.

174
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,720
I am not winking at you.

175
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,160
Where is the Osgood box?

176
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,360
You do know what
winking means, don't you?

177
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:44,320
You're sending out
some very mixed messages here.

178
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,960
You know I'm
over 2,000 years old.

179
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:47,720
I'm old enough
to be your messiah.

180
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,920
I am not winking at you.
Where is the box?

181
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,560
We're gonna need some wheels.
The van.

182
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,320
Okay, non-verbal
communication.

183
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,680
I assume that
you never bothered to learn Morse code.

184
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,200
Specs, setting 137.

185
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,640
Tell me!

186
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,200
-(BUZZING)
-Okay, we'll have to try something else.

187
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,400
Twenty questions.

188
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:08,680
Where's your pod?
Is it in a tunnel? Is it in London?

189
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,960
Thanks very much. Gotcha.

190
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:13,200
-(OPENS DOOR)
-(CAR UNLOCKS)

191
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:14,800
Stay where you are, Clara.

192
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,080
We're coming to get you.

193
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:18,840
And for God's sake,
don't let her into your memories.

194
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:21,560
Memories?
What memories, what has she got?

195
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:23,560
Don't tell her
where the Osgood box is.

196
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:26,120
And above all
don't tell her what it is.

197
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,480
(BEEPING)

198
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,920
-(STARTS ENGINE)
-(TYRES SCREECHING)

199
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:40,120
-Obviously, the Zygon could hear that.
-Obviously.

200
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:43,120
So, she's going to poke around
inside Clara's mind looking for answers.

201
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,120
The mind of Clara Oswald.

202
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,920
She may never
find her way out. (CHUCKLES)

203
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,160
I don't think I've ever
seen you smile before.

204
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,000
Dazzling, isn't it?

205
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,720
-Oh, I got a ping on Clara's phone.
-(BEEPS)

206
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,680
It's the location Bonnie
sent the text from.

207
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,800
A shopping centre, South London.

208
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:03,720
Ah, London, perpetual city,
cradle of culture, here we come.

209
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:06,320
Clara, stay safe.

210
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:08,680
OSGOOD:
She's posted a video link.

211
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:13,600
NEWSCASTER: A video supposedly
showing an alien in South London

212
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:16,000
-is posted across the Internet.
-(BEEPS)

213
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:18,120
OSGOOD: This is the same place
Bonnie texted from.

214
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,440
We need to hurry.

215
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,320
(STATIC)

216
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:47,480
Hello.

217
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:51,920
(STATIC)

218
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,440
Oh, there's no
point turning over.

219
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:56,000
There's nothing better
on the other side.

220
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,480
I could erase your mind.

221
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,240
Then why haven't you?

222
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,480
Having trouble?

223
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:11,200
Let's see what I can do.

224
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,360
(GRUNTS)

225
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,120
(PANTING)

226
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,000
(CHUCKLES)

227
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:24,840
See, this thing
works two ways, you know.

228
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,920
I want those memories.

229
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,200
The trouble is,
you're asking me for them,

230
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,240
which means you
can't access them, right?

231
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:32,560
I can make you tell me.

232
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:35,240
No, you can't, otherwise,
you would have done already.

233
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,000
I can kill you.

234
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:41,240
Go on then.

235
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,640
You think you're calling my bluff?

236
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,680
I am calling your bluff.

237
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:46,960
You need me alive.

238
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:48,800
Only as a source of information.

239
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,240
Then you better
start asking questions.

240
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,000
-You better not lie.
-(CHUCKLES)

241
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,880
You see, that's the problem.
I am a brilliant liar.

242
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:56,040
How are you
ever going to know?

243
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,880
Oh, Clara.

244
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:00,840
For a moment
I thought you were clever.

245
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,840
(HEART BEATING)

246
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,400
Our hearts are linked.

247
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Beat for beat.

248
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:11,560
The one thing you and I
can never do is lie to each other.

249
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,280
(GASPS)

250
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:14,360
(CHUCKLES)

251
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,040
Oh, that scared you, didn't it?

252
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:23,200
(TYRES SCREECHING)

253
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:27,720
London.

254
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,760
-What a dump.
-London's okay.

255
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:33,080
-No, it's not. It's a dump.
-(DOG BARKING)

256
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:35,760
You spend an awful lot of time here
considering it's a dump.

257
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:39,520
I spent an awful lot of time
being kidnapped, tortured, shot at,

258
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,560
exterminated.
Doesn't mean I like it.

259
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:44,160
Well, this is where
the video was shot.

260
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:46,560
Bonnie was here.
Come on, Doctor.

261
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,760
There's electricity
in the air.

262
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:04,000
It stinks.
It smells like barbecues.

263
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,800
Oh.

264
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,120
(BUZZING)

265
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:21,080
Now, listen to me.

266
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,400
Here's what we're going to do.

267
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,680
I'm going to ask you questions,

268
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:25,240
and if you don't tell me the exact

269
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:27,880
and complete truth,
I will know and I will kill you.

270
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,440
Do you understand me?

271
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,640
Yes.

272
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:36,960
I will slaughter you in that pod
right now. Am I lying to you?

273
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,440
No.

274
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:40,920
Good. Then we'll begin.

275
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,520
Where is the Osgood box?

276
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,320
You will answer me, Clara.

277
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,440
Truth or consequences.
Lie and you die.

278
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,200
Where is it?

279
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:53,440
UNIT HQ,
under the Tower of London.

280
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:55,640
-Where specifically?
-The Black Archive.

281
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:56,840
Ah, yes.

282
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:00,160
The dark little storage
facility for forbidden alien tech

283
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:01,960
where all of this began.

284
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,640
Who has access to it?

285
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:05,800
The Osgoods.

286
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,160
Only the Osgoods?

287
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,480
The Doctor sealed it up
after the last time.

288
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:11,080
He didn't want
UNIT interfering with the ceasefire.

289
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:14,880
Don't avoid the question.
Do only the Osgoods have access?

290
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,680
The Doctor has access too.

291
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:19,960
Who else?

292
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:23,800
Ah, you.

293
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:27,040
You have access.

294
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,160
Yes.

295
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:34,920
Is it a key? Or a code?
No, a pass? A key-code.

296
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,400
Give it to me now.

297
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,040
I can't.

298
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:43,120
Interesting.

299
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:45,160
-You're not lying.
-No, I'm not.

300
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:47,360
-But you have access of some kind?
-Obviously.

301
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,480
Give it to me now.

302
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,760
I told you, I can't.
You know I'm not lying.

303
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,560
I can't give you access.

304
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:57,240
Okay. How do you get in there?
How physically do you get in?

305
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:59,640
-It's automatic.
-But how? Tell me.

306
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,000
The door is keyed
to my body print.

307
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:07,600
Ah, yes. Your body print.

308
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,960
You can't give me access
because I have access already.

309
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,880
-I'm you.
-Yes.

310
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:16,120
And what am I going to find?
What's in the Osgood box?

311
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,080
Clara?

312
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,640
The box ends the ceasefire.

313
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:26,120
So I'm told. How?

314
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:28,600
There's a button inside the box.

315
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:30,960
Press it. It will transmit a signal

316
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:33,400
that will unmask every
Zygon on the planet for up to an hour.

317
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,560
What's there to smile about?

318
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:37,840
Ah, mass panic.

319
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:41,640
Followed by war.
Every Zygon on our side at a stroke.

320
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:45,160
Twenty million Zygons

321
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:47,480
against seven billion humans.

322
00:20:47,560 --> 00:20:49,280
That's not a war you can win!

323
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:51,240
Then we will die in the fire

324
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,800
instead of living in chains.

325
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,560
Most of your own
kind don't want that.

326
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:58,120
Then it's time we stopped
giving them a choice.

327
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,640
It's time you asked
the most important question.

328
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,800
-Which is?
-I'm waiting.

329
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,080
Why is it called an Osgood box?

330
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:12,840
I'm not telling you.

331
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:15,520
Good. I've been looking
forward to hearing you scream.

332
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,640
I'm not telling you because
when you get to the Black Archive,

333
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:18,760
you'll find out for yourself.

334
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,800
And when you do,
you're gonna want to speak to me again.

335
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:27,120
Am I lying to you?

336
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,280
See you later.

337
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:35,680
(STATIC)

338
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,280
What's your name?

339
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,040
Osgood.

340
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:44,000
No, no, no, your first name.

341
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,040
And what's your first name?

342
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:49,440
Basil.

343
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:54,360
Petronella.

344
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,600
Let's just,
uh, stick with what we had.

345
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:03,800
I need to ask you.

346
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,680
Because it's important.

347
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:09,120
Because it might matter.

348
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:10,960
What's important?

349
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:13,400
Which one are you?
Human or Zygon?

350
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:16,800
(GROWLING)

351
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:23,040
(GROWLS)

352
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,440
(GURGLING)

353
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,600
Whoever you are,
we can help you.

354
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,000
It wasn't me.

355
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,000
They attacked me.

356
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:43,200
They saw me.
I had to... (GROANS)

357
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:46,760
It's okay. It's okay.
It's okay. It's okay.

358
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:49,680
A commander came.

359
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:52,440
She turned me back.

360
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,560
(GROANS)

361
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,520
We can help. We can help you.

362
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:00,520
-Doctor, we can help him, can't we?
-I'm not sure.

363
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:08,200
Please, come back! Come back!

364
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:14,240
North America.

365
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,480
Reporting back to High Command.

366
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:19,080
I'm going to the Black Archive.

367
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,840
-I'll open it up, you will follow.
-Of course.

368
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:23,680
But first, locate the Doctor.
If possible, duplicate him.

369
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:24,840
And then kill him.

370
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:28,040
It would be my pleasure.

371
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:36,920
I can't help you just now, but...

372
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,320
Why?

373
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:46,120
-I was happy like this. I was happy.
-I understand.

374
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,160
I._..

375
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:50,600
I can't change. I can't hide.

376
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:51,920
Let us help you.

377
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:53,320
No.

378
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:56,400
You're truth or consequences.

379
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:59,640
We're not. We're really not.

380
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:04,520
I'm not part of your fight.

381
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:09,120
I never wanted to fight anyone.
I just wanted to live here.

382
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:12,960
Why can't I just live?

383
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:14,680
We are on your side.

384
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,800
I'm not on anyone's side.

385
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:22,400
This is my home.

386
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:25,040
Listen. We are not them.

387
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,400
I can't go back now.

388
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:30,880
You've taken my life.

389
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:34,400
No. No, no, no.
Stop, stop, stop.

390
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,280
They will kill me.

391
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:56,240
There it is, Osgood.
There's their plan.

392
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,440
Unmask everyone.

393
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:01,840
Provoke fear, paranoia.
Provoke a war.

394
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,160
Doctor.

395
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,120
Kate, are you all right?

396
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,600
Of course I am.
Why wouldn't I be?

397
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:09,000
-It's just, I heard otherwise.
-I'm fine.

398
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:11,080
Doctor, we know where
the Zygon Command Centre is.

399
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:13,120
We know where Clara's pod is.
We can take you there.

400
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,200
Well, how very convenient,

401
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:16,600
because that's just exactly
what we're looking for.

402
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:22,360
And here it is.

403
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,960
The Black Archive.

404
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:27,520
I do like being you, Clara.

405
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:30,040
Everyone just
waves you on past.

406
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:31,920
Now,

407
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:33,720
how does this work?

408
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:36,280
(BEEPING AND BUZZING)

409
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:37,680
(CHUCKLES)

410
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:01,360
Oh, they like a good cave,
don't they?

411
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,400
How many of these
pods are occupied?

412
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,080
We don't know.

413
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:06,200
Which one is Clara's?

414
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,960
Well, that's strange.
It was here before.

415
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:14,760
Doctor, I think they're Zygons.

416
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:19,360
Oh, you cheeky little monkeys.

417
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,880
Normalise.

418
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:43,400
Well, Clara, I think
you're reaching the end of your...

419
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,120
(PHONE RINGS)

420
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:55,080
-The Doctor is here.
-Don't kill him. We need him alive.

421
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,160
What for?

422
00:26:57,240 --> 00:27:00,680
Because I just found out
why it's called an Osgood box.

423
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:03,440
There's two of them.

424
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:06,320
Two Osgoods, two boxes.
Operation Double. What did you expect?

425
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,040
What's in them, Doctor?
Tell me, now.

426
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:15,960
One box normalises all the Zygons.

427
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:18,000
-And the other?
-Destroys them.

428
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:21,960
Which is which?

429
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:24,800
(LAUGHS)
That would be telling.

430
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:42,280
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

431
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:52,560
Which box normalises the Zygons, Doctor?
Tell me or she dies.

432
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,520
No. This is war.

433
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:56,400
You pull the trigger,
you pay the price.

434
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,560
Kill her.

435
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,520
The blue one. The blue one.

436
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,880
The blue one
normalises all your people.

437
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:07,600
Are you lying?

438
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,560
Are you lying to me, Doctor?

439
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:13,320
No, I'm not. And when you open up
the box, you'll see I'm not lying.

440
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,120
Doctor.

441
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:24,720
Doctor!

442
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:29,240
Yeah. I know.

443
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:31,320
Bring him to me!

444
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,760
(GUNSHOTS)

445
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,440
Sorry, Doctor. Self-defence.

446
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,600
-Who are you?
-I'm me.

447
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,800
How did you survive?

448
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:54,360
Five rounds, rapid.

449
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:56,560
(SCREAMS)

450
00:28:57,880 --> 00:29:00,680
I'm sorry, Doctor.
I know you don't approve.

451
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:03,200
DOCTOR: Why does peacekeeping
always involve killing?

452
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:08,040
Is this the lot?

453
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:11,360
No, there are plenty more of them,
they were the nearest.

454
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:14,120
You are you?

455
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:15,760
I'm me.

456
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:17,480
But human or Zygon?

457
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:18,560
Me.

458
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:20,600
What are we dealing with?

459
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:23,000
Twenty million Zygons
about to be unmasked.

460
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,680
They don't know whether
they're human or not.

461
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,520
And you can't fight them,
not with soldiers.

462
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,120
Which leads me to
a very big question.

463
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,840
Oh, I was really
hoping that it wouldn't.

464
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:33,920
The Z-67, Sullivan's gas,
the gas that kills the Zygons,

465
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:35,120
you took it.

466
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:37,360
Well, you know how it is,
Daddy knows best.

467
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,320
That's what's in
the red box, yes?

468
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:42,160
Of course it is.

469
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:45,080
If I remember rightly, it causes a chain
reaction in the atmosphere,

470
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,080
turns every Zygon
on Earth inside out.

471
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,840
Let me negotiate peace.
You can't commit mass murder.

472
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,600
Then why did you
leave the gas with us?

473
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:53,920
The boxes are safeguards
for both species.

474
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,040
You agreed to that.

475
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,280
I never agreed to that!

476
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:58,880
Yes, you did. Then I wiped your memory.
And you agreed to that too.

477
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:02,280
But that's why there were two
Osgoods to police the ceasefire.

478
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:04,120
One human and one Zygon.

479
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:06,560
To keep the secrets,
keep the peace.

480
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:09,440
I'm sorry, Doctor, truly.

481
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:12,240
But the peace is failing already.

482
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,520
Come on.

483
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:33,160
It's no good, Bonnie.
You can't win.

484
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:37,360
I don't care.

485
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:40,720
Hi! Hello! Hello!

486
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,480
Oh, hello, hi!

487
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,520
Hi, stop this. Stop this, please!

488
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:46,360
Let me take both
of these boxes away.

489
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:49,680
We'll forgive. We'll forget.

490
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:52,200
And the ceasefire will stand.

491
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:53,280
No.

492
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,520
Doctor, which of these
buttons do I press?

493
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:02,920
Doctor, which one?
Truth or consequences?

494
00:31:03,440 --> 00:31:05,880
Truth or consequences?

495
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:14,520
DOCTOR: This is the moment
we've all been waiting for.

496
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,240
Make-your-mind-up time.

497
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:18,440
One of those buttons
will destroy the Zygons,

498
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:20,360
release the imbecile's gas.

499
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:24,200
The other one detonates the nuclear
warhead under the Black Archive.

500
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:27,480
It'll destroy
everyone in London. Bonnie!

501
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,720
Bonnie, sweetheart,
one of those buttons

502
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:34,320
will unmask every
Zygon in the world.

503
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:38,280
The other one cancels
their ability to change form.

504
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,760
It'll make them
human beings forever!

505
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:43,200
There are safeguards
beyond safeguards.

506
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:45,120
I did this on a very important
day for me.

507
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:47,080
And this ceasefire will stand.

508
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:48,160
This is wrong.

509
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,280
No, it's not.

510
00:31:49,360 --> 00:31:51,160
You are responsible
for all of the violence,

511
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:52,520
all of the suffering.

512
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:53,720
-No, I'm not.
-Yes.

513
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:54,840
-No.
-Yes.

514
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:57,920
You engineered this situation,
Doctor. This is your fault.

515
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,000
No, it's not, it's your fault.

516
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,080
I had to do what I've done.

517
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,480
So did 1.

518
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:03,280
We've been treated like cattle.

519
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,360
So what?

520
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:06,040
We've been left to
fend for ourselves.

521
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:08,160
-So has everyone.
-It's not fair.

522
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:12,240
Oh, it's not fair?
Oh, I didn't realise that!

523
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:13,720
It was not fair.

524
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:16,000
Well, you know what?
My Tardis doesn't work properly.

525
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:17,960
And I don't have my
own personal tailor.

526
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,200
The things don't equate.

527
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:22,520
These things have happened, Zygella.
They are facts.

528
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:26,240
You just want
cruelty to beget cruelty.

529
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:29,760
You're not superior to people
who were cruel to you.

530
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:32,760
You're just a whole bunch
of new cruel people.

531
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:37,040
A whole bunch of
new cruel people

532
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:40,560
being cruel to some other people
who'll end up being cruel to you.

533
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:43,600
The only way anyone
can live in peace

534
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:46,280
is if they're prepared to forgive.

535
00:32:48,640 --> 00:32:51,000
Why don't you break the cycle?

536
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:53,600
Why should we?

537
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:00,880
What is it that you actually want?

538
00:33:07,680 --> 00:33:08,680
War.

539
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:12,240
Ah, ah, right.

540
00:33:12,320 --> 00:33:15,000
And when this war is over,

541
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:19,000
when you have a homeland
free from humans,

542
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,720
what do you think
it's gonna be like?

543
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:22,120
Do you know?
Have you thought about it?

544
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:24,000
Have you given it
any consideration?

545
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:26,280
Because you're very close
to getting what you want.

546
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:29,560
What's it gonna be like?
Paint me a picture.

547
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:32,480
Are you gonna live in houses?

548
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:35,000
Do you want people to go to work?
Will there be holidays?

549
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:37,120
Oh, will there be music?

550
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:39,600
Do you think people will
be allowed to play violins?

551
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,840
Who's gonna make the violins?

552
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,480
Well?

553
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:45,320
Oh, you don't
actually know, do you?

554
00:33:45,840 --> 00:33:50,160
Because, like every other
tantruming child in history,

555
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:52,240
Bonnie, you don't
actually know what you want.

556
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:57,160
So, let me ask you a question
about this brave new world of yours.

557
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:59,880
When you've killed all the bad guys,

558
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:02,880
and when it's all perfect
and just and fair,

559
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:06,320
when you have finally got it
exactly the way you want it,

560
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:09,040
what are you gonna do
with the people like you?

561
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:12,920
The troublemakers.

562
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:17,840
How you gonna protect
your glorious revolution

563
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:19,760
from the next one?

564
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:23,800
-We'll win.
-Oh, will you?

565
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:26,880
Well, maybe. Maybe you will win.

566
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,440
But nobody wins for long.

567
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:32,960
The wheel just keeps turning.

568
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:36,200
So, come on.

569
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:38,080
Break the cycle.

570
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,240
Why are you still talking?

571
00:34:40,320 --> 00:34:43,160
Because I want to get you to see,
and I'm almost there.

572
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:46,280
Do you know what I see, Doctor?

573
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:49,200
A box.

574
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:51,960
A box with everything I need.

575
00:34:52,040 --> 00:34:53,560
A 50% chance...

576
00:34:53,640 --> 00:34:55,000
For us too.

577
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,520
And we're off!
Fingers on buzzers!

578
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:02,080
Are you feeling lucky?
Are you ready to play the game?

579
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,880
Who's gonna be quickest?
Who's gonna be luckiest?

580
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,080
This is not a game!

581
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:07,120
No, it's not a game, sweetheart.

582
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:08,640
And I mean that most sincerely.

583
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:09,720
Why are you doing this?

584
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,600
Yes, I'd quite
like to know that too.

585
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:12,880
You set this up, why?

586
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:14,920
Because it's not a game, Kate.

587
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:18,440
This is a scale model of war.

588
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:22,920
Every war ever fought,
right there in front of you.

589
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:24,800
Because it's always the same.

590
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:28,760
When you fire that first shot,
no matter how right you feel,

591
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:31,200
you have no idea who's going to die!

592
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:36,120
You don't know whose children
are going to scream and burn.

593
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:39,240
How many hearts will be broken!

594
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:42,960
How many lives shattered!

595
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,320
How much blood will spill
until everybody does

596
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,800
what they were always gonna
have to do from the very beginning.

597
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:49,920
Sit down and talk!

598
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:53,040
(SIGHS)

599
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:55,760
Listen to me, listen.

600
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,200
I just...
I just want you to think.

601
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:01,440
Do you know what thinking is?

602
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:04,040
It's just a fancy word
for changing your mind.

603
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:06,640
I will not change my mind.

604
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:08,120
Then you will die stupid.

605
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:13,040
Alternatively, you could step
away from that box,

606
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:15,400
you could walk right
out of that door,

607
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:17,640
and you can stand
your revolution down.

608
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:20,800
No. I'm not stopping this, Doctor.

609
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:23,040
I started it, I will not stop it.

610
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:25,440
You think they'll let me go
after what I've done?

611
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:29,640
You're all the same,
you screaming kids, you know that?

612
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:31,280
"Look at me, I'm unforgivable."

613
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:33,680
Well, here's the unforeseeable,
I forgive you.

614
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,480
After all you've done.

615
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,320
I forgive you.

616
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:44,520
You don't understand.

617
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:48,960
You will never understand.

618
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:51,160
I don't understand? (LAUGHS)

619
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:52,560
Are you kidding me?

620
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:53,840
Of course, I understand.

621
00:36:54,760 --> 00:36:57,160
I mean, you call this a war?
This funny little thing?

622
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,760
This is not a war!

623
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:01,960
I fought in a bigger war
than you will ever know.

624
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:04,200
I did worse things
than you can ever imagine.

625
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,960
When I close my eyes...

626
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:11,840
I hear more screams than
anyone could ever be able to count.

627
00:37:12,080 --> 00:37:14,080
And you know what you do
with all that pain?

628
00:37:14,840 --> 00:37:16,840
Shall I tell you where you put it?

629
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,640
You hold it tight,

630
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:22,320
till it burns your hand.

631
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,320
And you say this,

632
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:29,040
"No one else will ever
have to live like this.

633
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:32,800
"No one else will
have to feel this pain.

634
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:34,320
"Not on my watch."

635
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,000
Thank you.

636
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:51,920
Thank you.

637
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:54,480
I'm sorry.

638
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,000
I know.

639
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:58,360
I know. Thank you.

640
00:38:00,600 --> 00:38:01,800
Well...

641
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,120
It's empty, isn't it?

642
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:34,600
Both boxes, there's nothing in them.

643
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:37,240
Just buttons.

644
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:44,320
Of course.

645
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:47,480
But you know
how you know that?

646
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:51,800
Because you've
started to think like me.

647
00:38:56,160 --> 00:38:57,720
It's hell, isn't it?

648
00:38:58,040 --> 00:39:00,000
No one should have
to think like that.

649
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:03,360
And no one will.

650
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:07,920
Not on our watch.

651
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,680
Gotcha!

652
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,560
How can you be so sure?

653
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:28,000
Because you have
a disadvantage, Zygella.

654
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,960
I know that face.

655
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,600
This is all very well,
but we know the boxes are empty now.

656
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,520
We can't forget that.

657
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:43,520
DOCTOR: No, well, uh...

658
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:45,760
You've said that the last 15 times.

659
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:04,520
You didn't wipe my memory.

660
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:08,520
No, just Kate's.

661
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:11,000
Oh, and your little friends
here, of course.

662
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:12,280
When they wake up,

663
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:13,640
they won't remember
what you've done.

664
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:15,360
It'll be our secret.

665
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:16,600
You're going to protect me?

666
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:19,640
You're one of us now,
whether you like it or not.

667
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:22,320
I don't understand how
you could just forgive me.

668
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,720
Because I've been where you have.

669
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:29,880
There was another box.

670
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:32,160
I was gonna press another button.

671
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:36,480
I was gonna wipe out
all of my own kind.

672
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:40,640
Man, woman and child.
I was so sure I was right.

673
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,360
What happened?

674
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:46,440
Same thing that happened to you.

675
00:40:47,600 --> 00:40:50,200
I let Clara Oswald
get inside my head.

676
00:40:56,400 --> 00:40:57,600
Trust me,

677
00:40:58,720 --> 00:41:00,360
she doesn't leave.

678
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:29,960
Zygon High Command,
the ceasefire is back in place.

679
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:31,640
The rebels are standing down.

680
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:33,760
You are all...

681
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,480
Safe.

682
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:51,600
The Tardis.

683
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:53,440
The Tardis.

684
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,120
What does it stand for?

685
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:57,080
What?

686
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,480
You're kidding me.

687
00:41:58,560 --> 00:41:59,960
Surely you know that.

688
00:42:00,040 --> 00:42:01,840
Well, I've heard a couple
of different versions.

689
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:03,720
I made it up from the initials.
It stands for

690
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:05,720
Totally Radically
Driving In Space.

691
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:08,760
Do you want to come?

692
00:42:09,720 --> 00:42:12,560
All of the future, all of history,

693
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:14,880
and all of the universe.

694
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:18,000
More than anything.

695
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:21,080
But I think I have to stay.

696
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:23,920
I've got a couple of boxes
to keep an eye on,

697
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:26,040
and a world to keep safe.

698
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:29,800
Fair enough.

699
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:34,840
Clara, would you mind, uh...

700
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:36,600
Mind what?

701
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:40,000
I'll see you in the Tardis, okay?

702
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:43,360
Er, yeah, sure.

703
00:42:46,160 --> 00:42:47,840
Take care, you.

704
00:42:47,920 --> 00:42:49,320
You take care of him.

705
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:51,000
Don't let him die or anything.

706
00:42:51,080 --> 00:42:52,360
What if he's really annoying?

707
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,160
-Then, fine.
-Got ya.

708
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:03,160
I need to know. Which one are you?

709
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:05,200
I'm Osgood.

710
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:07,080
Human or Zygon?

711
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:10,000
I'll answer that question one day.

712
00:43:11,040 --> 00:43:13,200
And you know when
that day will be?

713
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:14,760
The day nobody
cares about the answer.

714
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:20,000
Gotcha.

715
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:22,800
Oh, look at his face.

716
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:24,920
It's almost not fair.

717
00:43:26,120 --> 00:43:28,360
But I don't... How, how...

718
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:30,200
Think it through, Doctor.

719
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:31,960
It wouldn't be right, would it?

720
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:33,560
To carry on using Clara's face.

721
00:43:33,640 --> 00:43:34,720
When there's a vacancy.

722
00:43:35,320 --> 00:43:37,640
-Zygella?
-Osgood.

723
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:41,240
But which one of you...

724
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:42,480
-Osgood.
-Osgood.

725
00:43:43,480 --> 00:43:45,000
It doesn't matter
which of us is which.

726
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:46,920
All that matters is
that Osgood lives.

727
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:48,680
And nothing's going to stop us.

728
00:43:49,920 --> 00:43:53,080
You're a credit
to your species, Petronella Osgood.

729
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:55,120
No, Basil.

730
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:57,760
We're a credit to both of them.

731
00:43:59,280 --> 00:44:00,880
Oh, and you should know.

732
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:03,880
I'm a very big fan.

733
00:44:15,040 --> 00:44:16,760
So, you must have thought
I was dead for a while.

734
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:18,640
-Yeah.
-How was that?

735
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:22,800
Longest month of my life.

736
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:25,000
It could only have
been five minutes.

737
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:29,280
I'll be the judge of time.

738
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:50,200
Ice creams?

739
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:52,960
Yes, ice creams, then back to work.

740
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:55,080
What's today?

741
00:44:55,160 --> 00:44:57,400
You know, same old, same old.

742
00:44:58,000 --> 00:44:59,280
Defending the Earth.

743
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:15,640
RASSMUSSEN:
You must not watch this.

744
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:17,960
You can never unsee it.

745
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:21,520
NAGATA: Twenty-four hours ago
this station fell silent.

746
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:23,200
We've come to find out why.

747
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:25,240
CLARA: What are these?
CHOPRA: Morpheus.

748
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:27,040
DOCTOR: What is Morpheus?

749
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:30,680
The Morpheus machine concentrates
the whole nocturnal experience.

750
00:45:30,760 --> 00:45:32,560
Now you can go
a whole month without sleep!

751
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:33,640
Time is money.

752
00:45:33,720 --> 00:45:35,000
DOCTOR: Congratulations, Professor.

753
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,320
You've conquered nature.

754
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:38,600
You've also created an abomination.

755
00:45:38,840 --> 00:45:39,840
(CREATURE ROARING)

756
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:41,400
-Run! Run! Run!
-(GUNFIRE)

757
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:44,640
You can't stop them.
None of us can.

